The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 A man strangled his wife to death and hanged himself in Howrah early on Friday. A neighbour found Botke Bag, 35, hanging from a mango tree in a field beside his house at Jhingra, under Jagatballavpur police station, around 5 am. 

 e rushed to Bag?s house and found wife Rina lying dead in her bedroom. The couple leaves behind a son and two daughters, aged between eight and 13. Police superintendent Akhil K. Roy said Rina often quarrelled with her daily-wager husband over his drinking habit.

 A private bus mowed down a man in his 70s in Padmapukur Lane, under Beniapukur police station, early on Friday. The man was taken to Calcutta National Medical College and Hospital, where he was pronounced dead. The driver fled with his vehicle. 

 Six persons were detained by police in Baruipur, on the city?s southern fringes, on Friday after 15 metal biscuits were found in their possession. The six were on their way to Calcutta. The biscuits have been sent for tests.

 Two men and a woman were critically injured when the autorickshaw they were travelling in was hit by a police van near Baruipur police station, on the southern fringes of the city, on Friday evening. The injured were admitted to Baruipur Sub-Divisional Hospital.

 Several lawyers of the Howrah court, including members of the Criminal Bar Association and Criminal Bar Library, organised an agitation in front of the district judge?s room over the decision to hear criminal cases related to the railways in a separate court, at Howrah station, from Monday.

 The body of an 11-year-old boy was found floating in the Hooghly near Dhania Ghat, under North Port police station, on Thursday night. Police said Sambhu Pasi, a resident of Chitpur, was taking a bath in the river along with his friends.

 Nababarsher Baithak, a Bengali New Year programme, will be telecast on DD-I and DD-Bangla channels between 7 am and 9 am on Saturday, officials said.

